<br>
Websters defines a warrior as &quot;a man engaged or experienced in warfare&quot;. Simple, but that could be anyone not definite enough to have a class of people called Warrior rather than anything else.<br>
<br>
Time might be better spent looking at what people would call a warrior maybe you picked because of the various archetypes rolled into one class here are a few that I can think of however there are probably more.<br>
<br>
The Militia : One that fights motivated by the urge to protect ones home and family from things that threaten them, Weather man or beast they stand against them to till the end knowing that if they do not win all is lost.<br>
<br>
The Berserker : A fierce foe who uses massive strength to strike fear into their enemies and rally their allies. Raging threw a battle as others would wade in a sea crushing everything on the way to victory.<br>
<br>
The Weapon Master: Live by the sword, die by the sword. Using a blade or any other weapon with more skill and finesse than most people could attain they carve their way into history besting many people across many lands.<br>
<br>
The Conqueror : The leader of armies and nations. Master of Tactics and Strategy, laying siege to all, subjugating everything under your power.<br>
<br>
There are many reasons why people would have picked Warrior, why did you? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a>
